# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Canonical .dockerignore for vpc-runner builds
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This is the source-of-truth .dockerignore for projects that build the
# vpc-runner image. It is meant to be copied into (or merged with) the
# consumer's existing .dockerignore at the root of their build context.
#
# The biggest win: excluding `**/.terraform/` (Terraform provider plugin
# cache, ~170 MB on a populated checkout). Providers are re-downloaded on
# `terraform init` from the lock file, so the cache never needs to be in
# the image.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Terraform provider cache — never ship this in an image; `terraform init`
# will re-download providers from the lock file. Defensive: matches at
# any depth in case the build context contains nested terraform/ dirs.
**/.terraform/
**/.terraform.lock.hcl.bak

# OS / editor debris
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.tmp
*.bak

# Local-only files that should never end up in a build context
.env
.env.local
.env.example
*.log

# Node / Python virtualenvs (rare in a vpc-runner context, but safe)
node_modules/
venv/
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
